03/12/2007
PRISTINA, Kosovo, Serbia -- A blast inside a strip club in the town of Prizren, 80km south of Pristina, late Sunday (December 2nd) injured seven people, including one Bulgarian and one Albanian. 
Police spokesman Veton Elshani said on Monday that at least two people sustained serious injuries. 
Police have conducted several raids on the club related to human trafficking and prostitution. 
(DPA, Focus, BNR - 03/12/07)
